Update Project Theme to Match Screenshot Design
The current DFA Minimizer project has 6 color themes (indigo, midnight, emerald, sunset, ocean, amber). The user wants to replace them with 2 themes that match the PlacementCRM-style screenshots: a dark mode (deep navy + purple accents) and a light mode (white/lavender + purple accents).

Proposed Changes
Theme Color Palette (extracted from screenshots)
Dark Theme ("dark")

Token	Color	Description
bg-primary	#0b0f1a	Deep navy page background
bg-secondary	#111827	Card / sidebar backgrounds
bg-tertiary	#1a2035	Elevated card sections
bg-elevated	#1e2640	Hover/elevated surfaces
accent	#8b5cf6	Purple accent (buttons, active elements)
accent-hover	#7c3aed	Deeper purple on hover
gradient	#6366f1 → #8b5cf6	Purple gradient (profile header, brand)
border	#1e293b	Subtle dark borders
text-primary	#e8ecf4	White text
text-muted	#7882a0	Muted sidebar / secondary text
Light Theme ("light")

Token	Color	Description
bg-primary	#f0f2f8	Soft lavender-white page background
bg-secondary	#ffffff	White cards
bg-tertiary	#f5f7fb	Light elevated sections
accent	#7c3aed	Purple accent
accent-hover	#6d28d9	Deeper purple hover
gradient	#6366f1 → #8b5cf6	Same purple gradient
border	#e2e5f0	Soft lavender borders
text-primary	#111827	Dark text
text-muted	#6b7280	Gray secondary text
CSS Theme Variables
[MODIFY] 
index.css
Remove all 6 existing theme variable blocks (indigo, midnight, emerald, sunset, ocean, amber)
Add 2 new theme variable blocks: [data-theme="dark"] and [data-theme="light"] (light as :root default)
Colors will match the screenshot palette above
All remaining CSS (components, layout, buttons, etc.) stays the same — they already use var() tokens
Navbar Theme Picker
[MODIFY] 
Navbar.jsx
Replace the 6-item THEMES array with 2 items: { id: 'light', name: 'Light Mode' } and { id: 'dark', name: 'Dark Mode' }
Replace the palette-picker button icon (🎨) with a sun/moon toggle icon
Theme dropdown becomes a simple toggle button (click to switch between light ↔ dark) instead of a dropdown menu
App Default Theme
[MODIFY] 
App.jsx
Update the default theme fallback from 'midnight'/'indigo' to 'dark'/'light' based on system preference
Home Page Hardcoded Colors
[MODIFY] 
Home.jsx
Replace hardcoded hex colors (#1f2937, #6b7280) with CSS variable references (var(--text-primary), var(--text-muted)) so they respond to themes
About Page Hardcoded Colors
[MODIFY] 
About.jsx
Replace hardcoded #9ca3af with var(--text-faint) so footer text responds to themes
Verification Plan
Manual Verification (Browser)
Run npm run dev in the Sem-Project directory
Open the app in browser
Verify the dark theme matches the deep navy + purple style from the first screenshot
Toggle to light theme and verify it matches the white/lavender + purple style from the second screenshot
Navigate across all pages (Home, Input DFA, Results, Visualize, About) to confirm no broken colors or hardcoded values
Check that the theme toggle persists on page reload (localStorage)